cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on neural architecture search for computer vision tasks, specifically large-scale image classification and image super-resolution. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of stochastic gradient descent for training, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves optimization under resource constraints, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses channel pruning, which is a technique used in natural language processing and could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
